note.para:
This means that, if your application server supports EL, MMBase variables can also be directly accessed using EL (and inversely). For example:
<mm:field name="title" id="title" < , ${title}
will write the title field twice.

section.para:
This will write out the field 'title' six times:
<mm:field id="title" name="title" /> simple <mm:write referid="title" /> referid <mm:write value="$title" /> MMBase dollar sign notation <mm:write value="${title}" /> MMBase dollar sign notation with curly brackets, or EL if available <mm:write value="$[title]" /> MMBase dollar sign notation with square brackets (introduced to provide way to avoid collisions with EL) ${title}
Do you understand the difference between the 'value' and the 'referid' attributes?
